			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've not actually commanded a war, but we just sucessfully executed one last night. Some of the info I was able to glean from it is this...
<br />
Have at least two bards stay back (around the northern most huts) to highsun any giants back that get through. In waves two and three, we had at least one giant in each group get through that needed to be highsun'd back. When the giants start running for thurg, they run fast (with SoW wasn't able to gain on them).
<br />
Avoid fighting near the spearmen. They are permrooted, summon, and throw spears at you if you're too close. We had planed to kill some of them between waves, but the shouting that we were expecting at the end of each wave didn't happen, so we didn't know when one wave ended until the next wave began (giants were named differently).
<br />
In each group, kill the General or Warlord last.
<br />
There are five types of groups. One spawns south around the river, one spawns to the east and moves west to the river and turns north, one spawns east and moves north to the needle and turns west, one spawns west and moves east towards river and turns north, and the 5th one spawns west and moves north up mountain then turns east towards thurg. Knowing which type of group has spawned allows your armies to intercept at the right place.
<br />
It only takes one giant to get to the waterfall to end your war.
<br />
The more dwarf camps you keep alive, the more loot you get at the end.
<br />
Make sure everyone knows what your loot distribution policy is. During these wars, you can get a bunch of people wanting to join up who are looking for faction. If you are the one doing the turn-in, you pretty much get to decide what that policy is. It can generate a lot of bad blood if a bunch of people come to help thinking they would get a chance at some of the loot only to get left out.
<br />
If you fail at the war, you do keep whatever is needed to trigger another one. I don't know enough about the ring quest to know exactly what that is, but the guy who did it last night had failed at one a few weeks ago (our learning experience) and he said he could easily try it again (just needed the trigger npc to spawn again).</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
