			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've never organized one, so I too will suggest you find someone who's conducted one before or a detailed walkthrough. But I'll add an obvious point or two:
<br />

<br />
Loot:
<br />
Definitely shout out the loot plans before the raid, and I'd suggest even during the raid. People come and go for this thing (3+ hours long sometimes). Not all will be familiar with the loot distribution. Some won't even join if loot isn't awarded. Let them know what will be rolled on and what will be kept by the organizer. I suggest you allow most to be rolled on (except maybe the crown, which no one ever lets it get rolled on). More loot means more people.
<br />

<br />
I went on ring war recently and at the end found out that all loot was being bid on by the organizing guild first, <span style="font-style: italic">THEN</span> whatever was left was available for general /random. A damn nice earring (eye of Narandi or wretched or something like that?) was won by a organizing guild member who bid 1 (ONE) DKP for it for an ALT. Needless to say, there were quite a few pissed people.
<br />

<br />
Leadership:
<br />
Get someone to lead the raid who does nothing but lead. If he's fighting too, he'll probably miss something. A good leader can keep the various assembled masses in order and interested.
<br />

<br />
Tracker:
<br />
Get a tracker to stand at the dorf huts and do nothing but track and /rs the giant pops.
<br />

<br />
Positioning:
<br />
There is a large tree South of the dorf huts along the river. In between waves, make sure everyone gathers around the tree. It's central to the zone and people can get rebuffed, healed, SoWd and anything else they need while there.
<br />

<br />
Backup:
<br />
Definitely, if there are enough people, have a "backup group" stationed at the dorf huts. Inevitably, a giant or two is going to make it past the defense and scurry for Thrug. Keep a bard or two handy for gating them back to their spawn point (already mentioned).
<br />

<br />
There is a lot more, but that’s all my limited experience can lend.
<br />

<br />
~Ahsano<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://home1.gte.net/res03rwh/mo/ahsano.gif" border="0" />
