			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've led 8 of these without a failure yet. The best guide to this event I've found is at <a href="http://www.gpcentre.net/evercrack/10thwar.html" target="_blank">http://www.gpcentre.net/evercrack/10thwar.html</a>
<br />

<br />
Some observations:
<br />

<br />
- You will not lose your 9th ring nor your dagger if you fail. You will lose your 9th ring on the final turn in for the 10th ring.
<br />
- Personally, I will not start a war without 5 full groups of 60ish characters, because I refuse to waste everyone's time. I'm sure it can be done with less, but I won't risk it.
<br />
- Make hotkeys for all the instructions to Zrelik. I find it's most convenient to just spam the zone continuously for ALL dwarves to come to you. That way, there's less chance that one of the Coldain heroes will die, and a better chance you'll get his loot when you're done.
<br />
- People who are KOS to Thurgadin can make things difficult. If they insist on participating, make sure they either stand and die or train the PoK book if they get agro. Do not allow them to train Thurgadin. If any giant makes it to Thurgadin, you're done.
<br />
- Do your colleagues a favor and announce in advance (in /ooc and/or /shout) that you will be starting the war. Give them time to leave the zone in an orderly fashion. All XP MOBs despawn when the war starts, and people can get a little grumpy if you destroy their XP camp without giving them a heads-up. On the same note, offer to rez any innocent bystanders who inadvertently get in the way. Finally, note that pets will also despawn when you start the war, so have your pet classes wait until zone depop before summoning and buffing.
<br />
- Make sure people understand that every giant needs to be tanked before anyone casts on them. If a MOB is untanked and someone casts on him, he bolts directly for Thurgadin. Maintain situational awareness, and have everyone announce if runners head for Thurg.
<br />
- A backstop group is essential. Keep one group near the huts at all times, because double pops frequently occur from different directions. It's usually best to put the person directing the war in this group. Deaths are uncommon in our 10th ring wars, but the same group can serve as a rez/buff station if necessary.
<br />
- I find it's both efficient and effective to specify a single group to handle the spearmen once they pop. Just let that group start on one end and roll them right up, then move to the other side and deal with the second set of spearmen. All other groups should respond to moving MOB pops. The spearmen group can rejoin the main battle once the spearmen are cleared.
<br />
- Narandi is a big wuss (think "mini-Vindi"). He will disease slow your main tank, so make sure you have a PAL or CLR on cures so he can keep agro.
<br />

<br />
Good luck. This is one of the most fun events in the game, and the loot is awesome for the risk.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/ytrill/ytrill8.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27521" target="_blank" class="postlink">Hunter Ytrill Stonebow</a>
<br />
Forest Stalker of Tunare, Grand Master Fletcher
<br />
E'ci
